question: Which of the following is true about the prevalence levels in the regions shown on the map?

options.A: Region C has a higher prevalence than Region H.
options.B: Region A has a lower prevalence than Region B.
options.C: Region J has higher prevalence than Region G.
options.D: Region H has the same prevalence level as Region E.

explanation: The legend order misleads the actual comparison of prevalence levels between the regions.
